<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="538" pageId="6" pageNumber="537" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1845,2029]" pageId="6" pageNumber="537">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1845,1871]" pageId="6" pageNumber="537">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Greyish species with brownish legs, labrum about as long as head height, presutural supraalar seta fine, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[240,248,1900,1914]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="537">2</subScript>
abbreviated; male with scape and palpus with numerous rather long setae; female with mid femur with a few short posteroventral pennate setae apically, hind femur with ventral pennation on apical half.
</paragraph>
